{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (0 blocking, 20 advisory). Remediation of valid advisories,\nwith call sites verified against the code:\n\n- CORRECTION: `_verdict_manifest` lives at `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py:282`\n  (NOT attest.py). Plan-review manifest = `build_manifest` in\n  `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py`.\n- Git SHA idiom: reuse `src/rebar/signing.py:337 head_sha()` (a `git -C … rev-parse`\n  subprocess); resolver co-locates there. NOTE: the advisory's `run_git()` in\n  `gitutil.py` does NOT exist in this tree — that finding dismissed as invalid.\n- verify_signature typed contract to extend: `VerifySignatureResultOut` in\n  `src/rebar/mcp_server.py` + `src/rebar/schemas/verify_signature_result.schema.json`\n  (new nullable string field, e.g. `rebar_version`).\n- Build hook registration required: `[tool.hatch.build.hooks.custom]` in pyproject +\n  `hatch_build.py` at repo root + `artifacts` glob under\n  `[tool.hatch.build.targets.wheel]` + `.gitignore` entry — else the baked SHA never\n  ships to PyPI wheels (dead fallback).\n- `-dirty` rule DEFINED: dirty iff `git -C <dir of rebar.__file__> status --porcelain`\n  is non-empty (any staged/modified-tracked/untracked change in the rebar source tree).\n- Observability: when SHA resolution falls back live->baked->omit, no live SHA on a\n  git checkout should emit a debug log (silent-failure guard).\nThese are distributed into the three child stories below with file_impact set."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783123832176503001,"uuid":"f460381a-1a38-48c3-8ea5-d59cd63efbc0"}